  {
    "tool": "create_pull_request",
    "input": {
      "base": "main",
      "body": "## Summary\n\nThis pull request adds an issue-focused GitHub Actions automation system for the Node.js project.\n\n## What is included\n\n- Creates `.github/workflows/issue-automation.yml` for issue events (`opened`, `labeled`).\n- Adds automatic label management for category, priority, status, and first-time contributor labels.\n- Implements issue triage based on issue title/body keywords with highest-priority keyword matching.\n- Adds epic task breakdown automation that creates four linked sub-issues and updates the parent with a GitHub task-list checklist.\n- Adds automatic issue responses for bug, epic, and maintenance issues.\n- Adds milestone assignment to `v1.0.0` for high and critical priority issues.\n- Adds issue templates for bug reports, feature/epic requests, and maintenance requests.\n\n## Workflow behavior\n\n- All human-authored issues receive `needs-triage` during triage, then move to `needs-review` after the automated response.\n- Bug titles receive `bug`; epic titles receive `epic`; maintenance titles receive `maintenance`.\n- Priority is detected from title or body, with critical taking precedence over high, medium, and low.\n- First human issue authors in this repository receive `first-time-contributor` and a welcome message.\n- Epic issues generate exactly four sub-issues for requirements, design, implementation, and testing/documentation.\n\n## Files added\n\n- `.github/workflows/issue-automation.yml`\n- `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.md`\n- `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature_request.md`\n- `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/maintenance_report.md`",
      "draft": false,
      "head": "issue-management-workflow",
      "maintainer_can_modify": true,
      "owner": "mangowhoiscloud",
      "repo": "mcpmark-cicd",
      "title": "Implement Issue Management Automation Workflow"
    },
